                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="472612" author="JIRAUSER19288" created="Tue, 23 Sep 2025 14:06:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This can be reproduced on Rocky 9.4 and Lustre 2.16.58 due to an uninitialized pointer in &quot;__gen_ssk_prime()&quot;. Steps to reproduce:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;$ lgss_sk -f fs1 -t server -d /dev/urandom -p 512 -w /tmp/fs1.key
Reading random data for shared key from &apos;/dev/urandom&apos;
$ cp /tmp/fs1.key /tmp/fs1_cli.key
$ lgss_sk -t client -m /tmp/fs1_cli.key
Generating DH parameters, this can take a while...
Segmentation fault (core dumped)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;S&#233;bastien mentioned patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60624&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60624, &lt;/a&gt;which fixes this issue as part of some restructuring. The patch was recently landed on master (pending 2.16.59).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
